🎨 1. Visual Layout Improvements

✅ Group alignment
	•	Center-align the groups vertically in the available area.
	•	Add subtle padding and consistent spacing (e.g., setContentsMargins(20, 10, 20, 10)).

✅ Use icons
	•	Add icons to buttons such as:
	•	📞 Dial
	•	📲 Answer
	•	❌ Hang Up
	•	🔁 Redial
	•	You can use QPushButton.setIcon(QIcon("media/phone.png")) for that, and keep icons small (16–20px).

✅ Expand/collapse animation
	•	Instead of just showing/hiding the sections abruptly, you can add a smooth expand/collapse using QPropertyAnimation on the height of each group.

✅ Visual separation
	•	Add subtle frame borders or colored headers per group, for example:

group.setStyleSheet("""
    QGroupBox {
        border: 1px solid #0078D7;
        border-radius: 6px;
        margin-top: 10px;
    }
    QGroupBox::title {
        subcontrol-origin: margin;
        subcontrol-position: top center;
        padding: 3px 10px;
        color: #0078D7;
        font-weight: bold;
    }
""")


🧠 2. Usability Enhancements

✅ Dynamic State Changes
	•	Disable “Answer” when no incoming call exists.
	•	Disable “Hang Up” until a call is active.
	•	Show the current call state (Idle, Ringing, Active) via a colored label.

✅ Audio & Volume Controls
	•	For Audio Settings, include:
	•	Speaker & Mic volume sliders (QSlider).
	•	A mute/unmute toggle button.

✅ Advanced Call Handling
	•	Add “Hold”, “Swap”, and “Conference” as optional buttons.
	•	Make them appear dynamically only when those features are available.

✅ DTMF Controls
	•	Use a simple dial pad layout (3x4 grid of buttons 1–9, *, 0, #).
	•	Each sends SendDTMF() over DBus when clicked.

⸻

⚙️ 3. Code Organization

To keep your UI modular:
	•	Create separate methods:
	•	create_basic_controls_ui()
	•	create_audio_settings_ui()
	•	create_dtmf_controls_ui()
	•	Then load them into collapsible sections, like you already have, to maintain structure.

